You're confusing, or conflating, inflation with the inflation rate, which is current;y 3.2%.  The rest of your commentary can be corrected/adjusted based on that.  For prices to go down, the inflation *rate* would have to be negative, which would be deflation.  In general, prices go up over time, for a variety of reasons, some controllable some not.</p></div>
